  <!-- Main prose -->
  <section class="container-wide py-12">
    <div class="prose-dark max-w-4xl space-y-16">

      <!-- What is an AEO platform -->
      <div id="what-is-an-aeo-platform" class="scroll-mt-24">
        <span class="eyebrow">Definition</span>
        <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold grad-text">What Is an AEO Platform?</h2>
        <p class="mt-6"><strong>An AEO platform is an end-to-end solution that connects AI citation measurement, content optimisation, and reporting into a unified workflow, enabling organisations to run a systematic answer engine optimisation programme rather than a collection of disconnected tasks.</strong></p>
        <p>The distinction between a platform and a standalone tool matters practically. A standalone tool performs one function — tracking how often your brand appears in AI-generated answers, or generating structured data markup for a single page. A platform combines several of these functions, maintains a persistent record of performance over time, and typically provides workflow features that help a team act on the data it generates.</p>
        <p>Some platforms are software-only: they provide dashboards, data export, and optimisation recommendations that a client team implements independently. Others include a managed service layer, where the vendor's team operates the platform on the client's behalf, making changes, monitoring results, and delivering reporting on an ongoing basis. The managed-service model is common in the enterprise segment, where internal resource to run an AEO programme may be limited.</p>
        <p>The <a href="/generative-engine-optimisation/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">generative engine optimisation</a> discipline has matured enough that purpose-built platforms now exist. Evaluating them rigorously — against your specific objectives, programme stage, and budget — is what this guide enables.</p>

        <div class="mt-6 rounded-lg border border-[var(--accent)]/30 bg-[rgba(var(--accent-glow),.07)] p-5">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-[var(--accent)] uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">How this guide differs from our other AEO resources</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">This page evaluates <strong class="text-ink-100">integrated platform suites</strong> — solutions that bundle measurement, optimisation workflow, and reporting, evaluated on enterprise breadth and integration depth. It does not compare individual point tools by task. For that, see <a href="/top-aeo-software/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">Top AEO Software</a> (tools by job-to-be-done: snippet tracking, schema generation, answer-extraction testing, monitoring). For the full GEO tooling landscape across all four functional categories, see the <a href="/geo-tools/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">GEO Tools hub</a>. For hands-on tool assessments, see <a href="/reviews/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">GEO Reviews</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Platform categories -->
      <div id="platform-categories" class="scroll-mt-24">
        <span class="eyebrow">Market Map</span>
        <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold grad-text">Platform Categories in 2026</h2>
        <p class="mt-6"><strong>The AEO platform market in 2026 divides into four recognisable categories, each with a distinct primary value proposition, target buyer, and architectural approach.</strong></p>

        <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="card p-6 border-l-2 border-l-[var(--accent)]">
            <span class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-500">Category 1</span>
            <h3 class="mt-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-50">AI Visibility Measurement Suites</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Platforms built primarily around systematic querying of multiple AI platforms at scale. They send prompt sets to ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, Copilot, and other AI engines, record which brands and URLs appear in responses, and aggregate citation frequency data into dashboards with competitive benchmarking. The core value proposition is measurement: knowing your baseline and tracking change over time.</p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-500">Primary buyer: in-house SEO and content teams; digital agencies managing multiple clients.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card p-6 border-l-2 border-l-[var(--accent)]">
            <span class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-500">Category 2</span>
            <h3 class="mt-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-50">Retrieval-Augmented Content Platforms</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Platforms focused on the content layer: analysing which content is being retrieved by AI systems, identifying structural and semantic gaps that reduce citation likelihood, and providing content briefs or recommendations to address those gaps. These platforms typically integrate with a CMS or content workflow and are designed for ongoing content programmes rather than one-off audits.</p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-500">Primary buyer: content marketing teams; publishers with large content estates.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card p-6 border-l-2 border-l-[var(--accent)]">
            <span class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-500">Category 3</span>
            <h3 class="mt-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-50">Entity &amp; Knowledge Graph Platforms</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Platforms that focus on the entity layer: assessing how AI models understand and represent a brand, identifying gaps in knowledge graph presence (Wikipedia, Wikidata, structured data), and providing workflows to strengthen the authoritative signals that LLMs rely on when deciding whether to cite or describe an organisation. Less common than measurement suites but increasingly recognised as addressing a root cause of low AI visibility.</p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-500">Primary buyer: enterprise brands with complex entity structures; agencies specialising in GEO.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card p-6 border-l-2 border-l-[var(--accent)]">
            <span class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-500">Category 4</span>
            <h3 class="mt-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-50">Integrated SEO + AEO Suites</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Established SEO platforms that have added AI visibility modules alongside their existing rank tracking, backlink analysis, and site audit capabilities. These suites appeal to teams that want a single platform rather than a separate AEO tool. The depth of AEO functionality varies widely: some represent genuine investment in AI monitoring; others are lightweight features added to retain existing customers rather than serve AEO as a first-class capability.</p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-500">Primary buyer: teams already invested in a major SEO platform seeking to consolidate tooling.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Selection criteria -->
      <div id="selection-criteria" class="scroll-mt-24">
        <span class="eyebrow">Evaluation</span>
        <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold grad-text">Five Selection Criteria for AEO Platforms</h2>
        <p class="mt-6"><strong>Evaluating AEO platforms against a consistent set of criteria prevents vendor marketing from driving the decision — five dimensions determine whether a platform will deliver sustained value.</strong></p>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-6">
          <div class="card p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[rgba(var(--accent-glow),.15)] font-mono text-sm font-bold text-[var(--accent)]">1</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-50">AI Platform Coverage Breadth</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Does the platform monitor ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, and Copilot as a minimum? Does it include Google AI Overviews, Claude, and emerging AI assistants? A platform with narrow coverage will undercount your true AI visibility position, because your audience uses multiple AI systems. Evaluation question: ask the vendor specifically which AI platforms are covered and how frequently each is queried — not just which logos appear on their marketing page.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[rgba(var(--accent-glow),.15)] font-mono text-sm font-bold text-[var(--accent)]">2</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-50">Citation Tracking Granularity</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Does the platform track specific URLs cited, not just brand name mentions? Can it identify the position of a citation within a response (introductory mention, supporting source, recommended resource)? Does it distinguish between direct quotation, paraphrase, and incidental brand mention? URL-level attribution is what connects measurement data to a prioritised content action list. Without it, a platform tells you that something is happening but not what to do about it.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[rgba(var(--accent-glow),.15)] font-mono text-sm font-bold text-[var(--accent)]">3</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-50">Competitive Benchmarking Capability</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Can you track competitor citation rates for the same prompt sets? Does the platform show share-of-voice across AI platforms? Can you monitor specific competitor domains as citation sources? Competitive context transforms a citation frequency metric from a number into a strategic signal. Knowing that your brand appears in 28% of relevant AI answers is less useful than knowing that your closest competitor appears in 54%.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[rgba(var(--accent-glow),.15)] font-mono text-sm font-bold text-[var(--accent)]">4</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-50">Actionable Optimisation Workflow</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Does the platform connect measurement data to a clear optimisation action? Does it identify which pages have the highest citation potential and are currently underperforming? Does it generate structured recommendations — schema additions, content restructuring, entity signal improvements — rather than just reporting data? A platform that measures well but offers no pathway from insight to action requires a practitioner to build that bridge manually, which limits the return on platform investment.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[rgba(var(--accent-glow),.15)] font-mono text-sm font-bold text-[var(--accent)]">5</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-50">Data Methodology Transparency</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Is the vendor explicit about how AI response data is collected — official API access, proprietary crawlers, or third-party aggregation? How many times is each query run per reporting period, and how does the platform handle probabilistic variation in AI responses? What is the data retention period? Vendors who cannot clearly answer these questions introduce interpretive risk: you may be drawing strategy-level conclusions from statistically insufficient or methodologically opaque data.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Comparison table -->
      <div id="comparison-table" class="scroll-mt-24">
        <span class="eyebrow">At a Glance</span>
        <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold grad-text">Platform Type Comparison</h2>
        <p class="mt-6"><strong>Matching platform type to programme objective prevents over-investment in capability you will not use and under-investment in the capability you actually need.</strong></p>

        <div class="mt-8 overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)]">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--line)] bg-geo-900">
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-display font-semibold text-ink-100">Platform type</th>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-display font-semibold text-ink-100">Primary strength</th>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-display font-semibold text-ink-100">Best fit</th>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-display font-semibold text-ink-100">Watch out for</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-[var(--line)]">
              <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/50 transition-colors">
                <td class="px-4 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100">AI Visibility Measurement Suite</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-4 text-ink-300">Multi-platform citation tracking at scale; competitive benchmarking</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-4 text-ink-300">Establishing baseline; ongoing performance tracking; agency multi-client reporting</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-4 text-ink-300">Measurement without optimisation guidance; data without action</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/50 transition-colors">
                <td class="px-4 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100">Retrieval-Augmented Content Platform</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-4 text-ink-300">Content gap analysis; AI-readiness scoring; CMS workflow integration</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-4 text-ink-300">Large content estates; ongoing content programmes; publishers</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-4 text-ink-300">Limited AI platform coverage; proprietary scoring that is hard to interpret</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/50 transition-colors">
                <td class="px-4 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100">Entity &amp; Knowledge Graph Platform</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-4 text-ink-300">Addresses root-cause entity gaps; structured data and knowledge base workflows</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-4 text-ink-300">Enterprise brands; organisations with poor AI entity representation</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-4 text-ink-300">Slow to show measurable citation impact; requires specialist implementation</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/50 transition-colors">
                <td class="px-4 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100">Integrated SEO + AEO Suite</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-4 text-ink-300">Single platform for traditional and AI visibility; familiar interface for existing users</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-4 text-ink-300">Teams wanting to consolidate tooling; lower AEO programme maturity</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-4 text-ink-300">AEO functionality may be shallow; prioritise verifying actual AI coverage depth</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
